summary: Irene Becker (born 1952 in Hermsdorf, Berlin) is a German nurse, and serial killer, who killed at least 5 people by administering them drugs while working at the Charité clinic.

name: Irina Viktorovna Gaidamachuk
summary: Irina Viktorovna Gaidamachuk (Russian: Ирина Викторовна Гайдамачук, born 1972) is a Russian serial killer who killed 17 elderly women in Sverdlovsk Oblast between 2002 and 2010.

name: Jane Toppan
summary: Jane Toppan (March 31, 1854 – August 17, 1938), born Honora Kelley, was an American serial killer, nicknamed "Jolly Jane".

name: Jean-Baptiste Troppmann

Jean-Baptiste Troppmann (October 5, 1849 – January 19, 1870) 
was a French spree killer who between August 24 and September 19, 1869, murdered eight members of the Kinck family, including six children aged between 2 and 16 years old, in order to gain access to their money.

name: Jeanne Weber
summary: Jeanne Weber (7 October 1874 – 5 July 1918) was a French serial killer.

name: Jeffrey Lionel Dahmer

summary: Joel David Rifkin (born January 20, 1959) is an American serial killer who was sentenced to 203 years in prison for the murders of nine women between 1989 and 1993.

name: Johann Unterweger
summary: Johann "Jack" Unterweger (16 August 1950 – 29 June 1994) was an Austrian serial killer who committed murder in several countries.

name: Johannes Mashiane
summary: Johannes Mashiane, nicknamed The Beast of Atteridgeville, was a South African rapist and serial killer who was responsible for the deaths of 13 victims before committing suicide in 1989.

name: John Christie

name: John Emil List
summary: John Emil List (September 17, 1925 – March 21, 2008) was an American mass murderer and long-time fugitive.

name: John Eric Armstrong

name: John George Haigh
summary: John George Haigh (; 24 July 1909 – 10 August 1949), commonly known as the Acid Bath Murderer, was an English serial killer who was convicted for the murders of six people, although he claimed to have killed nine.

name: John Joubert
summary: John J. Joubert (July 2, 1963 – July 17, 1996) was an American serial killer executed in Nebraska.

name: John Martin Crawford

summary: John Martin (born John Martin Scripps, 9 December 1959 – 19 April 1996) was an English spree killer who murdered three tourists—Gerard Lowe in Singapore, and Sheila and Darin Damude in Thailand—with another three unconfirmed victims.

name: John Norman Collins
pseudonym: The Coed Killer, Michigan Murderer, The Ypsilanti Killer, John Chapman

name: John Paul Knowles
summary: Paul John Knowles (April 17, 1946 – December 18, 1974), also known as The Casanova Killer, was an American serial killer tied to the deaths of 20 people in 1974, though he claimed to have taken 35 lives.

name: John Thomas Straffen
summary: John Thomas Straffen (27 February 1930 – 19 November 2007) was an English serial killer who was the longest-serving prisoner in British history.

name: John Wayne Glover
pseudonym: The Granny Killer, North Shore Granny Killer
summary: John Wayne Glover (26 November 1932 – 9 September 2005) was an English-Australian serial killer convicted of the murders of six elderly women (aged from 60 to 93), over a period of 14 months from 1989-1990 including Winifreda, Lady Ashton, widow of the English-Australian impressionist painter Sir Will Ashton, in suburbs located in Sydney's North Shore.

name: John William Cooper
summary: John William Cooper (born 3 September 1944) is a Welsh serial killer and diagnosed psychopath.

name: José Antonio Rodríguez Vega
summary: José Antonio Rodríguez Vega (3 December 1957 – 24 October 2002), nicknamed El Mataviejas (The Old Lady Killer), was a Spanish serial killer who raped and killed at least 16 elderly women, ranging in age from 61 to 93 years old, in and around Santander, Cantabria, between August 1987 and April 1988.

name: José Luis Calva Zepeda
summary: José Luis Calva Zepeda (June 20, 1969 – December 11, 2007) was a Mexican writer and possible serial killer.

name: Joseph Christopher

name: Joseph Kallinger
summary: Joseph Kallinger (born Joseph Lee Brenner III; December 11, 1935 – March 26, 1996) was an American serial killer who murdered three people, and tortured four families.

name: Joseph Naso
summary: Joseph Naso (born January 7, 1934) is an American serial killer sentenced to death for the murder of six women.

name: Joseph Paul Franklin

name: Karl Denke

name: Kaspars Petrovs
summary: Kaspars Petrovs (born 1978) is a Latvian serial killer.

name: Keith Bernard Clay

pseudonym: The Merry Widow of Windy Nook

summary: Joseph Michael Swango (born October 21, 1954), also known under the aliases David J. Adams, Michael Kirk, Jack Kirk, and Michael Swan, as well as the press nickname Dr.

summary: Michel Paul Fourniret (born 4 April 1942), also known as the Ogre of the Ardennes, is a French serial killer who confessed to killing twelve people in France and Belgium between 1987 and 2003.

summary: Miyuki Ishikawa (石川 ミユキ, Ishikawa Miyuki, born 1897, date of death unknown) was a Japanese midwife and serial killer who is believed to have murdered many infants with the aid of several accomplices throughout the 1940s.

name: Moses Sithole

name: Nannie Doss
pseudonym: Arsenic Annie, Giggling Grannie, Giggling Nanny, The Jolly Black Widow
summary: Nannie Doss (born Nancy Hazel, November 4, 1905 – June 2, 1965) was an American serial killer responsible for the deaths of 11 people between some time in the 1920s and 1954.

name: Nathaniel Robert Code Jr.

name: Nathaniel White
summary: Nathaniel White (born July 28, 1960) is an American serial killer.

name: Norman Volker Franz
summary: Norman Volker Franz (born January 30, 1970 in Neheim-Hüsten, North Rhine-Westphalia) is a German murderer and fugitive who is being sought after by international arrest warrant.

name: Ōkubo Kiyoshi
summary: Kiyoshi Ōkubo (大久保 清, Ōkubo Kiyoshi, January 17, 1935 – January 22, 1976) was a Japanese serial killer.

name: Olaf Däter

name: Patrice Alegre

name: Patrick Baxter

name: Pedro Rodrigues Filho
summary: Pedro Rodrigues Filho (born 17 July 1954), also known as Pedrinho Matador (Killer Petey), is a Brazilian serial killer who pursued and killed other criminals.

name: Peter Britton Tobin

name: Peter Bryan
summary: Peter Bryan is an English serial killer and cannibal who suffers from schizophrenia and committed three murders between 1993 and 2004.

name: Peter Kudzinowski

name: Peter Kürten

name: Peter Lundin

name: Peter Norris Dupas

name: Peter Thomas Anthony Manuel

name: Peter William Sutcliffe

name: Peter Woodcock

name: Phillip Carl Jablonski

name: Pierre Chanal

name: Pierre Corneille Faculys Basson

name: Pierre Fernand Bodein

name: Posteal Laskey
